MINNA â€“ Professor Dantani Ibrahim Wushishi, the Registrar/ Chief Executive National Examination Council (NECO), has attributed the successes recorded by the examination body in both managerial and quality assurance to the constant training and retraining of members of staff. Professor Dantani disclosed this at the opening of a two-day workshop for director and other senior cadre of staff at its corporate headquarters along the Minna- Bida Road on Monday, expressing determination to be ahead in maintaining global best education standards in the conduct of all examinations. Assuring Nigerians that some noticeable challenges notwithstanding, NECO would not run short of international acceptability, Professor Wushishi told the select participants to the workshop on quality assurance. With the training and retraining of different categories of staff, particularly the senior cadre, the NECO boss said the council would continue to attain national and international recognition and respect amongst its peers as truly a viable examination body.